## 2026-05-27 ‚Äî Export fix, logo embed, AI_HANDOVER.md

### Export stack overflow fix
**Root cause:** `_b64(buf)` in `settings.js` used `String.fromCharCode(...new Uint8Array(buf))`.
Spreading a large ArrayBuffer (e.g. encrypted 2MB backup) as function arguments overflows the JS call stack.
**Fix:** Chunked loop ‚Äî 32KB chunks, `bytes.subarray(i, i + CHUNK)` spread per chunk.
**Applies to:** Both V2 and V3.

### Logo visible on new device
**Problem A:** After cloud load or file restore, `localStorage['qstore2_logo']` was not updated.
On the subsequent forced reload, the splash IDB read found the logo, but localStorage-dependent
boot paths didn't benefit from the restored data until the next settings visit.
**Fix A:** `sync.js loadFromCloud()` and `settings.js _doImportData()` now mirror `unitLogo` from IDB
to `localStorage['qstore2_logo']` immediately after `importAll()`.

**Problem B:** A fresh device opening a distribution HTML file sees no logo on splash before IDB is populated.
**Fix B:** New "Download unit copy" button in Settings ‚Üí Unit logo section. Serialises
`document.documentElement.outerHTML` and injects `<script>window.__UNIT_CONFIG__={logo,unitName,unitCode};</script>`
before `</head>`. Shell.js boot() reads `window.__UNIT_CONFIG__.logo` and writes to localStorage before
showSplash(), so the logo shows immediately even on first-ever open of the file.

